<DOC><DOCNO> AP890801-0220 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-01-89 0036EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f PM-AmericanExpress-Insurance     08-01 0173</FIRST><SECOND>PM-American Express-Insurance,0178</SECOND><HEAD>American Express To Sell Last of Fireman's Fund Common Stock</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   American Express Co. will sell the last of itscommon stock in Fireman's Fund Corp. back to the company for $342million in securities, the companies said.   American Express said Monday the transaction represented itsexit from the property and casualty insurance business, which itregarded as too up-and-down and a poor fit with the rest of itsbusinesses. The financial services giant continues to sell lifeinsurance, a business it entered through Fireman's Fund.   American Express bought Fireman's Fund for $350 million inpreferred stock in 1968 and began selling it piece by piece in1985. The sale of the final 15 percent brings total proceeds of thesale to $1.8 billion, the company said.   Fireman's Fund is paying for the stock purchase by issuing aspecial class of voting preferred stock to American Express. Thereare no restrictions on American Express' ability to trade thepreferred shares, which are redeemable after seven years.</TEXT></DOC>